  "narrative": "Spread of Acme Manufacturing LLC (borrower BRW-****4821) covering FY2024 and FY2025. Both periods balance (total assets equal total liabilities plus equity) and each computed subtotal ties to the reported totals; computed net income ties to reported net income in both years. Revenue grew 11.1% year over year and EBITDA grew 30.4%. FY2025 shows a current ratio of 2.4, debt-to-equity of 1.15, debt-to-EBITDA of 1.53, and an EBITDA-based DSCR of 2.86; the FY2025 operating cash-flow proxy is 167,000. The normalized view removes two documented non-recurring items in FY2025 (a 45,000 owner discretionary bonus added back and a 20,000 one-time gain removed), lifting normalized EBITDA to 345,000; each adjustment carries a document citation in the register. No mappings were flagged ambiguous, so no human mapping resolution is outstanding. This spread is analytical support for the credit file and requires credit-officer review before use.",
  "disclaimer": "Spread, ratios, and cash-flow figures are analytical support prepared from borrower-supplied documents and analyst-documented adjustments. They are not a credit decision, credit rating, eligibility determination, or investment advice, and are not an approval, a denial, or a recommendation regarding any facility. Figures depend on the accuracy of the source documents; a credit officer must resolve any flagged mappings and make all lending decisions."
